    "updated_at": "2014-06-04T21:56:38Z",
    "body": "Currently, `task::failing` will abort if you don't set a local task (it's using `Local::borrow`). Regardless it's not hooked up to the plumbing in unwinding, so it still has no concept of whether an unwind is in progress without consulting the local task.\n",
